criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  diagnosed with ischemic stroke and met the diagnostic criteria of the World Health
             Organization;

          -  initial stroke within seven days, with limb dysfunction;

          -  NIHSS scale consciousness scores of 0 or 1;

          -  provided informed consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  incomplete clinical data;

          -  having a physical disability or other diseases that affect the limb function;

          -  having cognitive impairment or other diseases that interfere with participation;

          -  having serious cardiopulmonary dysfunction or another disease that requires absolute
             bed rest;

          -  having progressive stroke or having severe complications that patients drop the study
             before completion.
